# HG Insights AI Presentation Pipeline

## Project purpose

Zero-touch presentation generation for HG Insights. Markdown decks in `decks/` are compiled by Slidev into static SPAs and deployed to Vercel. An LLM generates deck content; the build pipeline enforces brand compliance via a custom Slidev theme.

**Pipeline:** Cowork ‚Üí Google Drive (`.md`) ‚Üí GitHub sync ‚Üí Vercel CI/CD ‚Üí live URL at `/{slug}/`

**Live site:** https://ai-presentation-seven-omega.vercel.app
**Repo:** https://github.com/drewgilbert-lab/ai-presentation

---

## Architecture

```
decks/*.md                    ‚Üí Markdown source (one file = one presentation)
hg-theme/                     ‚Üí Custom Slidev theme (layouts, components, brand tokens)
build.js                      ‚Üí Scans decks/, builds each to dist/{slug}/
vercel.json                   ‚Üí Wildcard SPA routing rewrites per deck slug
scripts/sync-decks-from-drive.js ‚Üí Sync .md decks from Google Shared Drive
scripts/commit-deck.js        ‚Üí GitHub Contents API for direct deck commits
scripts/deck-validation.js    ‚Üí Shared deck validation for sync and commit-deck
.github/workflows/sync-decks-from-drive.yml ‚Üí Scheduled Drive ‚Üí GitHub sync
dist/               ‚Üí Build output (gitignored); do not edit manually
```

When modifying the build or theme, always run `npm run build` locally before pushing ‚Äî Vercel Linux is case-sensitive and stricter than macOS dev.

---

## Tech stack

- **Slidev** v0.49 ‚Äî Markdown ‚Üí Vue SPA
- **Vue 3** ‚Äî theme layouts and components
- **UnoCSS** ‚Äî brand colors and shortcuts in `hg-theme/uno.config.ts`
- **Node.js ESM** ‚Äî `build.js`, `scripts/commit-deck.js`, `scripts/sync-decks-from-drive.js`
- **Vercel** ‚Äî hosting and CI/CD

---

## Directory responsibilities

| Path | Purpose | Agent may edit? |
|------|---------|-----------------|
| `decks/` | Presentation Markdown source | Yes ‚Äî primary content output |
| `hg-theme/layouts/` | Cover and default slide shells | Yes ‚Äî brand chrome only |
| `hg-theme/components/` | Reusable Vue components (e.g. `HgStatBox`) | Yes ‚Äî sparingly; prefer HTML composition in decks |
| `hg-theme/public/` | Static assets (logos). **Must be lowercase `public/`** | Yes ‚Äî assets only |
| `hg-theme/uno.config.ts` | Brand color tokens and UnoCSS shortcuts | Yes ‚Äî brand changes only |
| `hg-theme/style.css` | Global typography | Yes ‚Äî typography only |
| `build.js` | Multi-deck build orchestration | Yes ‚Äî build logic only |
| `vercel.json` | Deployment routing (wildcard slug rewrites) | Yes ‚Äî routing changes only |
| `prompts/` | LLM system prompts | Yes |
| `.cursor/skills/` | Cursor agent skills | Yes |
| `dist/` | Generated build output | No ‚Äî regenerated by `npm run build` |
| `node_modules/` | Dependencies | No |

---

## Deck Markdown conventions (`decks/*.md`)

These rules are enforced by the theme, build, and `scripts/deck-validation.js` (used by sync and commit-deck).

### Required structure

- Slides separated by `---` on its own line
- **First slide:** `layout: cover` ‚Äî title on `#` line, subtitle as plain text
- **All other slides:** `layout: default` ‚Äî one `#` title per slide
- Filenames: **kebab-case** (e.g. `q3-strategy.md` ‚Üí live at `/q3-strategy/`)

### Allowed in deck content

- Standard Markdown (headings, lists, tables)
- Inline HTML with UnoCSS/Tailwind classes (no blank lines inside multi-line HTML blocks ‚Äî use spacing classes instead)
- Brand shortcuts: `hg-card`, `hg-stat-box`, `hg-stat-num`, `hg-stat-label`, etc.
- Brand color tokens: `text-hg-navy`, `bg-hg-gray`, `border-hg-royal`, etc.
- Layout utilities: `grid`, `flex`, `gap-*`, `mt-*`, etc.
- Slidev `v-click` for progressive reveal
- Components: `<HgStatBox num="..." label="..." />`, `<HgIcon name="..." />` (theme icons in `hg-theme/public/icons/`)

### Forbidden in deck content

- `theme:` frontmatter (use `layout:` only)
- Layouts other than `cover` and `default`
- Custom CSS (`<style>`, `@import`), inline `style="..."` except chart dimensions (`height`/`width` on bar/progress elements)
- Non-brand hex/rgb/hsl colors
- Custom Vue components not in `hg-theme/components/`
- External image URLs (logos and icons are provided by the theme)
- `<script>` tags
- Blank lines inside multi-line HTML blocks (Slidev renders following indented lines as raw code)

### Canonical reference

- Baseline deck: `decks/marketing.md`
- Full generation guide: `.cursor/skills/hg-slidev-deck/SKILL.md`
- Legacy prompt: `prompts/claude-system-prompt.md`

For complex visuals, compose HTML + brand UnoCSS classes ‚Äî do not create new Vue components unless explicitly requested.

---

## Theme conventions (`hg-theme/`)

### Layouts auto-apply brand chrome ‚Äî do not duplicate in decks

- **`cover.vue`:** Navy background, white logo top-left, CONFIDENTIAL bottom-right
- **`default.vue`:** White background, flex column layout ‚Äî body content in a clipped upper zone, fixed footer band below with vertically centered logo (left), copyright (center), slide number (right)

### Content safe zone

Default-layout slides reserve ~52px at the bottom for the footer. Body content auto-scales to fit above it. Do not embed `<Toc>` or slide sidebars in deck markdown. Deployed decks run in **deck-only mode** ‚Äî no Slidev navigation chrome (no sidebar, no bottom nav, no overview overlay). Invisible keyboard/swipe navigation still works for presenting.

### Logo assets

- Store SVGs in `hg-theme/public/` (lowercase ‚Äî critical for Vercel Linux builds)
- Import in layouts via `import logo from '../public/...'` ‚Äî do not use absolute `/logo.svg` paths in Vue files

### Brand colors (only these)

| Token | Hex |
|-------|-----|
| `hg-navy` | `#003366` |
| `hg-royal` | `#2D59A7` |
| `hg-medium` | `#3B86D4` |
| `hg-light` | `#BFE2F5` |
| `hg-red` | `#CC1E4C` |
| `hg-purple` | `#6E3191` |
| `hg-gray` | `#EAEBED` |
| `hg-dark` | `#424242` |

### Adding theme components

Only add Vue components when the same pattern is reused across many decks. Prefer deck-level HTML composition. New components go in `hg-theme/components/` and are auto-imported by Slidev.

---

## Build and deploy

### Commands

```bash
npm install                  # Install dependencies
npm run build                # Build all decks to dist/
npm run sync-decks             # Sync decks from Google Drive (local test)
npm run commit-deck -- --file decks/my-deck.md   # Push deck via GitHub API
npx slidev decks/marketing.md --theme hg-theme     # Preview single deck
```

### Build behavior (`build.js`)

- Wipes `dist/` before each build
- Builds every `decks/*.md` to `dist/{slug}/` with `--base "/{slug}/"` and `--theme hg-theme`
- Generates `dist/index.html` listing all decks
- Slidev CLI v0.49 does **not** support `--emptyOutDir` ‚Äî output dirs are cleared manually

### Adding a new deck ‚Äî required steps

1. Save `{slug}.md` (kebab-case) to the shared Google Drive folder (Cowork) or create `decks/{slug}.md` locally
2. Run `npm run build` locally to verify
3. For Cowork/Drive: wait for GitHub sync (~5 min) or trigger **Actions ‚Üí Sync decks from Google Drive**
4. For direct publish: `npm run commit-deck -- --file decks/{slug}.md` or git push

---

## Agent behavior guidelines

### Do

- Minimize scope ‚Äî focused diffs, no unrelated changes
- Match existing code style (ESM, minimal comments, no over-engineering)
- Run `npm run build` after changes to build, theme, or decks
- Reference `.cursor/skills/hg-slidev-deck/SKILL.md` when generating or editing decks
- **Always update [`CHANGELOG.md`](CHANGELOG.md) after every change** ‚Äî add an entry under `[Unreleased]` describing what changed and why
- Keep secrets in `.env` (never commit `.env` or tokens)

### Do not

- Edit `dist/` or `node_modules/` directly
- Rename `hg-theme/public/` to `Public/` (breaks Vercel builds)
- Use absolute `/logo.svg` paths in theme Vue files
- Commit without user request
- Add dependencies without justification
- Create markdown files the user did not ask for (except when implementing a requested feature)

---

## Environment variables

See `.env.example`. Required for `commit-deck`:

- `GITHUB_TOKEN` ‚Äî PAT with repo Contents write access
- `GITHUB_OWNER` ‚Äî default `drewgilbert-lab`
- `GITHUB_REPO` ‚Äî default `ai-presentation`

For local Drive sync testing (`npm run sync-decks`):

- `GDRIVE_FOLDER_ID` ‚Äî Shared Drive folder ID (`18cqtrCBfZ9w58_ZVa5mhAwVgtcgRuQbv`)
- `GDRIVE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON` ‚Äî service account key JSON string
- `SYNC_PRUNE` ‚Äî optional; set `true` to delete local decks not in Drive

